CHELICERAE (
Fig. 1C
) with movable digit 13 long, without tooth; fixed digit 14 (14–15) long, with a small subapical tooth and two vague medial teeth, pilus dentilis 3 (2–4). PALP (
Fig. 10A
) with trochanter devoid of seta; femur with three simple setae; genu bearing five simple setae; tarsal apotele two-pronged. HYPOSTOME (
Fig. 11A
) with only two pairs of hypostomal setae (
h1
and 
h2
); deutosternal groove present but weakly developed, without rows of denticles; corniculi horn-like.

Idiosoma ( Figs 3A & 3B , Table 2 ) 227 (211–234) long along midline, 99 (98–99) wide at level of s4 , DORSUM: podonotal and opisthonotal shields discernible. Podonotal shield with nine pairs of attenuate setae and three pairs of lyrifissures ( id2 , id4 and idla ) and a pair of big solenostomes ( gd2 ), j3 , z2 and z4 longer than those in larval stage; lateral setae longer than medial setae, s4 longest. Muscle marks present between j3 and j4 , j5 and j6 . Opisthonotal shield with four pairs of setae ( J5 , S5 , Z4 and Z5 ), six pairs of lyrifissures ( idm4 , idm5 , idm6 , idl3 , idl4 and idx ) and a pair of solenostomes ( gd9 ), J5 , S5 and Z4 smooth and short, Z5 long, serrated and knobbed apically. Three pairs of setae ( J2 , S2 , Z1 ) and four pairs of lyrifissures ( idm2 , idm3 , idl2 and is1 ) present on integument between podonotal and opisthonotal shields; S2 long and apically blunt. Lateral cuticle with setae r3 and R1 present. Stigmata located ventrolateral to coxae III and IV. Peritremes extending beyond level of j6 . VENTER ( Fig. 3B ): sternal area without discernible shield, with three pairs of setae ( st1 , st2 and st3 ) and two pairs of lyrifissures (
iv1 and iv2
). Four pairs of opisthogastric setae ( JV1 , JV2 , JV5 and ZV2 ) present on cuticle around anal valve, a pair of paranal setae ( pa ) and a postanal seta ( po ) of subequal length present around anal valve.

Spermathecal apparatus (
Fig. 7D
). Cervix cup-shaped, atrium oval and connected with cervix, with slender minor duct; major duct long and narrow.

